          <h3>Ductless Mini Split Systems</h3>
          <p>Zoned comfort without ductwork. Perfect for additions, older homes, or creating separate comfort zones.</p>

          <h3>Packaged Units</h3>
          <p>All-in-one systems for homes with limited indoor space. All components housed in a single outdoor unit.</p>

          <h3>Dual Fuel Systems</h3>
          <p>Combines a heat pump with gas furnace backup for optimal efficiency year-round.</p>

          <h2>Why Proper Installation Matters</h2>
          <p>Studies show that improper installation can reduce HVAC efficiency by 30% or more. Common installation problems include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Incorrect Sizing:</strong> Oversized or undersized systems waste energy and fail to maintain comfort</li>
            <li><strong>Improper Refrigerant Charge:</strong> Too much or too little refrigerant reduces efficiency and damages compressors</li>
            <li><strong>Ductwork Problems:</strong> Leaky or undersized ducts waste conditioned air</li>
            <li><strong>Airflow Issues:</strong> Poor airflow causes uneven temperatures and premature wear</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Our certified technicians follow manufacturer specifications and industry best practices to ensure your installation performs as designed.</p>

